After applying the Dark theme, **ALL settings sub-pages** (Appearance, Profile, Account, Notifications, Display) show a **severe visual anomaly at the bottom**:

- ❌ **Dark area below content**: The page body/background switches to dark mode color (near-black, `hsl(224 71.4% 4.1%)` or similar), creating a large dark block below the content area
- ❌ **White content area**: The main content panels/cards remain white/light colored (not switching to dark mode)
- ❌ **Inconsistent theming**: The page is NOT fully in dark mode - only the background switches while form elements, cards, labels remain in light mode
- ❌ **Color mismatch**: This creates a jarring visual contrast between the white content and the dark empty space below

